We use Audio RMS Batch Nodes to modify the effect and motion scale of AD based on vocal and instrumental audio intensity (z-scores)

Upscale image frame by frame while using RAVE to ensure consistency. You can remove the rebatch nodes and reuse ad_model if the upscaled images fits in your VRAM. You can also try increasing the resolution of the upscaled image to 1080x720 or 1620x1080 (or any aspect ratio consistent with your img_w and img_h inputs) if you have access to larger VRAM.

- img_w and img_h are the native image dimensions you use to create keyframes
- ad_w and ad_h are animatediff dimensions, they're smaller to ensure everything fits in your VRAM
- fps is native frames you render your video at
- multiplier is the frame interpolation to use in the final processing step
- global seed will keep all your seeds consistent without manually changing each node
